Diagnosis. Dorsally dark green to brownish green on head, pronotum, scutellum and connexivum; hemelytron brown with embolium yellowish. Head, pronotum and scutellum with large dark punctures. Embolium with punctures contrastingly darker than the rest of hemelytron. Apex of scutellum with a large yellow to reddish cordiform spot (
Fig. 53
). Venter yellow or orange (
Fig. 60
), densely punctate with abdominal punctures darker and larger than thoracic punctures. Antennae and legs yellow.

Thorax. Pronotum with anterolateral margin yellow. Anterior half of scutellum with punctuation deep and large on black spots; posterior half with fine punctures; large yellow cordiform calloused spot punctate at least proximally (
Fig. 53
). Ventral surface with punctuation uniformly and densely distributed. Evaporatorium whitish, rugulose and not punctate. Peritreme yellow and short, not reaching middle of the distance between ostiole and lateral margin of metapleuron. Arms of the anterior bifurcation of metasternal process wide and divergent, receiving fourth segment of rostrum; apex of arms rounded (
Figs. 9–10
). Legs not punctate or maculate.

Abdomen. Dorsal surface with fine concolorous and uniformly distributed punctures. Connexivum with dense and uniformly distributed concolorous punctures, central part of each segment with a calloused impunctate spot (
Fig. 53
). Ventral surface with pseudosutures and intersegmental areas concolorous; punctures dark and uniformly distributed except on medial impunctate region (
Fig. 60
).

Female genitalia. Gonocoxites 8 setose, convex, punctuation dark or concolorous but concentrated on inner part, distal rim acuminate. Laterotergites 8 with concolorous punctures deep and uniformly distributed, distal margin slightly acuminate with a small black spine reaching or passing laterotergites 9 . Gonocoxites 9 setose not punctate, proximal margin slightly tumid and barely overlapping gonocoxites 8 . Laterotergites 9 setose with basal half deeply excavated and distal part slightly tumid, apex acuminate (
Fig. 12
) and black. Pars intermedialis oval (
Fig. 11
).

Male genitalia. Pygophore. Dorsal rim deeply punctate and corrugated; posterolateral angles tumid (
Fig. 13
) and impunctate. Superior processes of genital cup curved, slightly constricted medially and distally barely concave (
Fig. 15
). Parameres with two lobes rising from base: one larger, subrectangular with apex, slightly curved passing dorsal rim; the other digitiform, long and directed lateroposteriorly (
Fig. 15
). Posterior face of proctiger rounded and slightly concave; lateral excavation delimited dorsally by large black carinae (
Fig. 15
). Ventral rim with large, dense brown punctures; bottom of medial excavation with a thin carina. Expansions of ventral rim large pyramidal or subconical (
Figs. 14–15
). Phallus with distal acuminate process developed; vesica oblong (
Fig. 16
).

Distribution (
Fig. 66
): MEXICO : Sinaloa, Aguascalientes, Jalisco, State of Mexico , Guerrero, Puebla, Morelos, Oaxaca, Tabasco.
